column4: I'm having an issue booting directly off of the Live CD for ubuntu 8.10. What is the best channel to get help?
Here is the place. Any errors or symptons it is giving may be helpful in diagnosis
I get a lot of errors when I try to run it
They all look similar to this one: [112.143392] end_request: I/O error, dev sr1, sector 36856
Did you check the CD when you burned it to make sure the MD5 checksum was correct? It may be a bad image or burn
what's the best way to check the checksum?
I can't boot from the Live CD for 8.10, and my CD checks out!!! I'm very frustrated and confused!
Yes, but fairly busy. Did you find how to check the MD5 sums of the cd image you downloaded or burned to make sure it was not corrupt?
I ran the CD's self-check and that ran fine
Is this some Asus p5k   type motherboard?
You might find more Mac-specific help in #ubuntu-powerpc   The mac versions are not officially supported in this channel
also no one is in that channel
Thats just the channel name. Many there are running various mac platforms and are helpful with things like EFI booting, etc
but there's no one there now
n/m that was weird, they are there now
